      • compare

        @RequestMapping(method=POST,
                value="compare",
                produces="application/json")
public org.springframework.http.ResponseEntity<String> compare​(@RequestBody
                                                               String payload)
        Returns difference between two JSONs in JSON Patch format. JSONs to compare have to be valid and be under properties "json1" and "json2" in body of HTTP request.
        Parameters:
        payload - body of HTTP request
        Returns:
        difference between two JSONs as HTTP response
        Throws:
        JSONException - if given JSON doesn't have "json1" or "json2" properties or JSON is invalid

      • extract

        @RequestMapping(method=POST,
                value="extract",
                produces="application/json")
public org.springframework.http.ResponseEntity<String> extract​(@RequestBody
                                                               String payload)
        Returns JSON with removed properties specified in JSON array. JSON has to have two properties "json" that contains JSON to extract from and property "keys" that is a JSON array of strings.
        Parameters:
        payload - body of HTTP request
        Returns:
        JSON with no given properties
        Throws:
        JSONException - if given JSON payload doesn't have "json" or "keys" properties or JSON is invalid

      • filter

        @RequestMapping(method=POST,
                value="filter",
                produces="application/json")
public org.springframework.http.ResponseEntity<String> filter​(@RequestBody
                                                              String payload)
        Returns JSON with properties specified in JSON array. JSON has to have two properties "json" that contains JSON to filter in and property "keys" that is a JSON array of strings.
        Parameters:
        payload - body of HTTP request
        Returns:
        JSON with only given properties
        Throws:
        JSONException - if given JSON payload doesn't have either "json" or "keys" properties or JSON is invalid
